sentences.sContent: The landscape has remained predominantly rural in appearance.
sentences.sCn: 该风景看上去主要保留了乡村风貌。

sentences.sContent: ...movement out of city centers was widespread and downtown tenants were predominantly made up of the working poor...

words.tran: 主要的；卓越的；支配的；有力的；有影响的

trans.tranOther: You use predominantly to indicate which feature or quality is most noticeable in a situation
